    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> It may be running the ! commands using Windows' cmd.exe rather than git bash.\n\nProbably not. The commands `ls` and `mktemp` are not windows commands. They are not available when starting `cmd.exe`. And remember it works for me with a normal file, i.e.\n\n``` ipython\ntmp=\"foo\"\n!ls -la $tmp\n!echo asdf > $tmp\n```\n\njust works.\n"
